* "''A catalogue of nebulae and clusters of stars in the southern hemisphere, observed at Parramatta in New South Wales.'' ''[[Philosophical_Transactions_of_the_Royal_Society|Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society]]'', Vol. '''118''', p. 113—151, 1828. This catalogue with descriptions contains 629 southern deep-sky objects.
* He also discovered and catalogued 256 southern [[double_stars|double stars]] in "''Approximate Places of Double Stars in the Southern Hemisphere, observed at Paramatta in New South Wales.''", which was published in the ''Memoirs of the [[Royal_Astronomical_Society|Royal Astronomical Society]]'' ''Mem.Ast.Soc.London'', Vol. '''3''', 257, 1829.
